external_knowledge:
- "sailor" metaphorically represents 'investor';
- "vessel sails under the flag with the number zero" refers to 'investor_id = 0';
- "waves they ride" metaphorically represents 'transaction_type';
- "treasures they seek or surrender" metaphorically represents 'amount'.

sql:
SELECT t.transaction_id, t.company_id, t.investor_id, t.transaction_type
FROM transactions t
JOIN (
    SELECT DISTINCT company_id
    FROM stock_splits
) ssc ON t.company_id = ssc.company_id;

external_knowledge:
- 'stars' metaphorically refer to companies; 'shone in the sky of the stock market' refers to going public through IPO;
- 'top three brightest' means the top three companies based on the most recent IPO date;
- 'at least two' refers to a condition where there should be a count of at least two such companies per sector.

sql:
SELECT sector_id, AVG(market_cap) AS average_market_cap
FROM companies
GROUP BY sector_id;

external_knowledge:
- "active in the past year" refers to companies that have declared dividends after the current date minus one year;
- "downloading data extensively" means downloading more than three times within the last year;
- "their representatives" refers to users with the role 'company'.

sql:
SELECT DISTINCT c.company_name
FROM companies c
JOIN stock_splits ss ON c.company_id = ss.company_id;
